# Session test topology bootstrap

`alwaysApply` on sibling rules is **not sufficient**. At the **first substantive turn** of every session — and again before any answer about **QA, housing sync, relay, entitlement, deploy, or multi-device behavior** — you **must** use the **Read** tool on **all** of these files (do not skip because they are also always-applied):

| File | Why re-read |
| --- | --- |
| `.cursor/rules/conversation-test-context-discipline.mdc` | Whole thread + user test context; no refuted hypotheses |
| `.cursor/rules/no-blind-patching-evidence-first.mdc` | Evidence before patches; verify UI gates before retest steps |
| `.cursor/rules/melos-run-workflow.mdc` | How the user starts/stops apps (`./tool/melosw`, no `r`/`R`) |
