## Public URLs vs local-only (verify scripts; do not invent)

Read `mobile/tool/run_dev.sh`, `mobile/tool/run_dev_web.sh`, and `mobile/tool/entitlement_base_url_default.sh` when advising on env or URLs.

| Service | Typical prod URL | Who calls it |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Relay | `https://sync.incoherences.org` | All clients (web + Android) |
| Entitlement (HTTP API) | `https://license.incoherences.org` | Clients that perform register / roster / license calls |
| Relay → entitlement introspection | Private Docker URL on VPS | **Relay only** — not the browser |

**Script defaults (current repo intent):**

- **`run:dev` (Android/native):** `ENTITLEMENT_BASE_URL` defaults to `https://license.incoherences.org` when `API_BASE_URL` is prod sync.
- **`run:dev:web`:** `ENTITLEMENT_BASE_URL` defaults to `https://license.incoherences.org` when `API_BASE_URL` is prod sync (same as native). Requires CORS on the license vhost for `http://localhost:5001` — see `entitlement/deploy/apache2/license-vhost.conf.template`.

**Forbidden without evidence:**

- Suggesting `http://127.0.0.1:8081` for entitlement when the user tests against the **VPS** stack (that port is for a **local** relay+entitlement stack on the same machine as the client).
- Assuming web and Android share the same entitlement URL defaults.
- Inferring VPS `.env` values (`ENTITLEMENT_ENABLED`, tags, etc.) from gitignored `dev-ideas/` files — **verify** or ask.

